				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The OAM copying happens due to <strong>analog behavior</strong> in the original silicon, specifically DRAM voltage decay. Since Visual2C02 is a purely digital simulation, it will never be able to replicate that sort of thing perfectly.<br /><br />The fact that it's resetting anything at all is due to pure luck; the fact that it's going to the wrong column means it's probably just a timing glitch which I may or may not be able to fix.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Quietust, QMT Productions
<br />P.S. If you don't get this note, let me know and I'll write you another.</div>
